@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Version History";
}
@Styles.Render("~/Content/version.css")
<div class="update alpha">
    <p><b>v0.2</b></p>
    <div class="update">
        <p><b>v0.2.3</b> - July 15th 2015</p>
        <p>Features</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Geologist now available in the store.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Technical</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Server notifications can now be dynamically sent to all users. Information regarding downtime and other server affecting issues will be posted with this.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Geologist's effect has been fixed. Now unlocks Onyx, Quartz and Diamonds.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="update">
        <p><b>v0.2.2</b> - July 15th 2015</p>
        <p>Features</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Geologist now available in the store.</li>
            <li>When connecting after being online you'll be given a report of what happened while you were gone.</li>
            <li>Lumberjacks have been nerfed. This will lead into crafting and city changes in the coming patches.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Technical</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Server notifications can now be dynamically sent to all users. Information regarding downtime and other server affecting issues will be posted with this.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Potions now behave correctly when loading a save from offline.</li>
            <li>Sessions do not terminate until page refresh. (Should fix chat and reduce data usage!)</li>
            <li>Fuel is now correctly consumed during offline processing.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="update">
        <p><b>v0.2.1</b> - July 10th 2015</p>
        <p>Technical</p>
        <ul>
            <li>All connections are now encrypted.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Tutorial modals behave better.</li>
            <li>Slow initial load is handled more gracefully.</li>
            <li>Sessions terminate more reliably on page unload/refresh.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="update wipe">
        <p><b>v0.2.0</b> - July 9th 2015</p>
        <p>Features</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Added the marketplace. You can submit buy or sell orders that will be automatically fulfilled as other orders are submitted.</li>
            <li>Added a brief tutorial. This will be expanded on in the future along with a hint system.</li>
            <li>Achievements now give additional details when hovered.</li>
            <li>Buttons now change state to indicate whether or not you can interact with them.</li>
            <li>Added server notifications when attempting to perform illegal actions.</li>
            <li>Browser forced to clear cache on updates to avoid client-side visual issues.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Technical</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Massively overhauled user management system. Moderators will be selected from upstanding players.</li>
            <li>Users will now be tagged as alpha players. This will give you a benefit eventually!</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Crafting menu now correctly highlights resources that you do not have enough of.</li>
            <li>Fixed some minor UI issues.</li>
            <li>Fixed chat.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="update alpha">
    <p><b>v0.1</b></p>
    <div class="update">
        <p><b>v0.1.3</b> - May 6th 2015</p>
        <p><i>This is the last update before v0.2. A lot of great stuff will be coming in the future.</i></p>
        <p>Features</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Highscores can now be viewed at any rank. Navigate up or down the ranks or jump to a specific rank.</li>
            <li>Achievements have been added. Very primitive at the moment. In the future they will be expanded.</li>
            <li>When you log in you'll receive recently sent messages to allow you to jump into the ongoing conversation.</li>
            <li>Items that you have not yet discovered will not be shown in the Statistics or Inventory Configuration menus.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Experimental</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>Material Design</p>
                <p>I'm looking into changing the game's UI up a little bit. The achievements page is a preview of how the game might look if it is rewritten according to Google's standards. Let me know what you think!</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="update wipe">
        <p><b>v0.1.2</b> - April 27th 2015</p>
        <p>Features</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Gatherer page expanded to show more information.</li>
            <li>Furnace and Cauldron now require upgrades to unlock.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Store correctly updates.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Technical</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Ajax services refactored.
                <ul>
                    <li>Fail more gracefully.</li>
                    <li>Loading indicator added.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Chat system rewritten in preparation for friends chat, group chat, etc.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="update wipe">
        <p><b>v0.1.1</b></p>
        <p>Features</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Leaderboards added.</li>
            <li>Gatherers can now be disabled to stop them from consuming fuel and gatherering resources.</li>
            <li>Added particles to rock.</li>
            <li>Rock is now more obviously clickable.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Item quantities no longer overflow to negative.</li>
            <li>Oil consumption correctly rounds.</li>
            <li>Sell all items configuration window looks better at low resolutions.</li>
            <li>All gatherers now correctly gather resources after an offline period.</li>
            <li>Craftable upgrades now have descriptions.</li>
            <li>Player counter hopefully more accurate.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="update">
            <p><b>v0.1.1a</b></p>
            <p>Fixes</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Logging in now works correctly.</li>
                <li>Pickaxes correctly require the previous to purchase.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="update">
        <p><b>v0.1.0</b></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Initial release.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
